OL,6,FOxfam said it was "deeply concerning"
OL,7,Fthat international development
OL,8,Fexpertise has been a "casualty" of the
OL,9,F"ill-advised" merger.
OL,11,FA spokesperson for the charity said:
OL,12,F"There were plenty of warnings that
OL,13,Fthe biggest losers from the merger
OL,14,Fwould be people living in poverty
OL,15,Faround the world, yet the Government
OL,16,Fchose not to listen.
OL,18,F"Its decision to spend large parts of
OL,19,Fthe aid budget in the UK has made
OL,20,Fmatters much worse.
